other_tests.findings: Biopsy showed immature testicular tissue with seminiferous tubules but no Leydig cells.
A left testis was identified in the pelvis, surrounded by a Fallopian tube.
Bilateral gonads were found on the pelvic wall, connected to a lumbar pedicle attached to bilateral Fallopian tubes and vasa deferentia, associated with a midline hypoplastic uterus.
Serum AMH concentrations were, respectively, 327, 36, and 380 pmol/liter in S1 (10 yr), S2 (7 yr), and S3 (5 yr).
other_tests.changes_over_time: S2 was unexpectedly low for AMH; unfortunately, the assay could not be repeated.

other_tests.findings: The LH-releasing hormone test was normal.
